[32m│[0m Excellent! Now I have a clear picture of the reflection context and          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m filtering behavior. Let me analyze the key findings:                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## Analysis Summary                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Reflection Point:**                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Input is reflected **directly after the closing `</form>` tag**            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Context: `</form>\n    REFLECTED_INPUT\n</div>`                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The input is reflected as **plain text in HTML body** (not inside an       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m attribute)                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Filter Behavior Patterns:**                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Tags that get STRIPPED (no reflection):**                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `<iframe>`, `<svg>`, `<details>`, `<object>`, `<embed>`, `<marquee>`    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - HTML entities like `&lt;script&gt;` get stripped completely             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Tags that get CONTENTS extracted (tag removed, content kept):**         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `<script>alert(1)</script>` → becomes `alert(1)`                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `<SCRIPT>`, `<ScRiPt>` (case insensitive) → same behavior               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `<style>@import...</style>` → becomes `@import...`                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `<plaintext>test` → becomes `test`                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Nested tags: `<scr<script>ipt>` → inner `<script>` removed first        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Characters that PASS through:**                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Single quotes `'`                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Double quotes `"`                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Greater/less than `>`, `<` (when not part of filtered tags)             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Event handlers like `onload=`, `onmouseover=`, `javascript:`            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Key Insight:** The filter appears to be **removing specific HTML tags**    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m but **not escaping the content**. Since the input is reflected directly in   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m the HTML body (not in an attribute), I need to find tags that:               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Are NOT being filtered                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Can execute JavaScript                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Work in body context without user interaction                              [32m│[0m
